cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper is related to natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper deals with charge prediction for legal cases, which involves natural language processing. The paper also proposes a number learning network, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with legal cases, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
